        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('Ken Thompson'); ?>
        <?php echo $this->stencil->addHeadshot('Ken Thompson', 'jpg', 'left'); ?>
        <p><strong>Kenneth Lane Thompson</strong> (born 4 February 1943), is an American pioneer of computer science. Having worked at <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Bell Labs', 'C'); ?> for most of his career, Thompson designed and implemented the original <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Unix', 'OS'); ?> operating system. He also invented the <strong>B programming</strong> language, the direct predecessor to the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('C', 'L'); ?> programming language, and was one of the creators and early developers of the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Plan 9', 'OS'); ?> operating systems.</p>
        <p>Since 2006, Thompson works at <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Google', 'C'); ?>, where he co-invented the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Go', 'L'); ?> programming language.</p>
